36#include "krb5_locl.h"
37
38KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
39krb5_read_message (krb5_context context,
40 krb5_pointer p_fd,
41 krb5_data *data)
42{
43 krb5_error_code ret;
44 uint32_t len;
45 uint8_t buf[4];
46
47 krb5_data_zero(data);
48
49 ret = krb5_net_read (context, p_fd, buf, 4);
50 if(ret == -1) {
51 ret = errno;
52 krb5_clear_error_message (context);
53 return ret;
54 }
55 if(ret < 4) {
56 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
57 return HEIM_ERR_EOF;
58 }
59 len = (buf[0] << 24) | (buf[1] << 16) | (buf[2] << 8) | buf[3];
60 ret = krb5_data_alloc (data, len);
61 if (ret) {
62 krb5_clear_error_message(context);
63 return ret;
64 }
65 if (krb5_net_read (context, p_fd, data->data, len) != len) {
66 ret = errno;
67 krb5_data_free (data);
68 krb5_clear_error_message (context);
69 return ret;
70 }
71 return 0;
72}
73
74KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
75krb5_read_priv_message(krb5_context context,
76 krb5_auth_context ac,
77 krb5_pointer p_fd,
78 krb5_data *data)
79{
80 krb5_error_code ret;
81 krb5_data packet;
82
83 ret = krb5_read_message(context, p_fd, &packet);
84 if(ret)
85 return ret;
86 ret = krb5_rd_priv (context, ac, &packet, data, NULL);
87 krb5_data_free(&packet);
88 return ret;
89}

91KRB5_LIB_FUNCTION krb5_error_code KRB5_LIB_CALL
92krb5_read_safe_message(krb5_context context,
93 krb5_auth_context ac,
94 krb5_pointer p_fd,
95 krb5_data *data)
96{
97 krb5_error_code ret;
98 krb5_data packet;
99
100 ret = krb5_read_message(context, p_fd, &packet);
101 if(ret)
102 return ret;
103 ret = krb5_rd_safe (context, ac, &packet, data, NULL);
104 krb5_data_free(&packet);
105 return ret;
106}
